values: can't take a good day without a bad one.

sia is great.
her new album "colour the small one" is great. 
yeah, it is. 

and not just because "breathe me" is on it...because obviously i ordered the six feet under album with that song on it the day after i heard it. 
yeah, that's right.

I walked over to the hill where we used to go and sled. There were a lot of little kids there. I watched them flying. Doing jumps and having races. And I thought that all those little kids are going to grow up someday. And all of those little kids are going to do the things that we do. And they will all kiss someone someday. But for now, sledding is enough. I think it would be great if sledding were always enough, but it isn't.  - The Perks of Being a Wallflower

yeah i've been updating like a fiend. i'm suppose to be at work. the ONLY JOB I NOW HAVEEEEE YES. (for tims sake, in case he didn't hear) - i get my own office. i just run the entire business basically besides the "hands on" aspect of HVAC systems. it's sweet. i'm not at work because.....MY SISTER IS AT THE HOSPITAL SEEING IF THE LADIES ARE COMING TODAYYYYYY she's been having contractions since 4am and she is almost 35 weeks (twins usually go from 34-36 weeks sooooo they're ready!) if she's having them today i have to drive marissa to john's grandmoms house and then go to the hospital since i'm in the room! i am so excited! she's having a c-section so no gross pushing, sweating, cursing or ugly pink babies. just adorable, screaming, crying, unhappy, miserable bitches. hah. i have a problem. if it's not today - it'll be any day now. but let's hope it's today cause i'm excited!!!!!!!!!!! keep you updated - since i'm now officially back into the LJ game.

finals = ass pain. dammit. i'm in the library right now. i should be working on the fucking paper that is due in a week that i JUST found out i have. anyone want to do it? it's on affirmative action. that's all i know. and it's SO HARD to find information on this topic believe it or not. i was considering not doing it. then i slipped that to my mom and she flipped...so there goes that idea b/c she's going to be on my ass about it. last weekend was NYU. 'twas pretty sweet. chags came up saturday after getting lost for like half a day. we got rather shitayy that night, and caused a bit of a rutkus (thats a difficult one to spell), but i had a great time. i'm suppose to go up to NYU again saturday (or sunday) for the REMMYS which is like this award show thang for jake's program and he's playing his song there w/a live band. so i really wanna go. but if i don't get this paper done, no. i must not. I'M MOVED OUT OF HERE A WEEK FROM TODAY. HOLL-ER. i'm done my freshman year of college 2 weeks from today. i have classes mon/tues then i'm off till the following monday where i have one final then the next day 3 and then FINISHEDDDDD. i have an interview for J.B. Dawson's for friday. hopefully thatll go well. hollywood tans said they might call. i doubt they will. i need a job so fucking bad it's not even funny i am LITERALLY worth $35 that is my moms. yeah. i'm completely serious. i blew through any money i had this summer and from breaks that i worked at einsteins with. screwed. and i need a job since i'm commuting next semester to keep myself occupied from being home all the time since bill is moving in and i'm not that happy about it. MY BIRTHDAY IS NEXT THURSDAYYYYYYYYYYYY. which means i get my sweet RAZR phone. and verizonnnn. if i dont get the dark pink razr, i will be a brat and be a tad upset. then immediatley get over it since I DON'T HAVE NEXTEL ANYMOREEEEE. sweet. will post my new # asap. need college to be over. now. forever. ok. thanks. bye. yeah.

i wish i could've gone to the snow dance - that would've been awesome.
i'm just so busy w/work (i'm working this weekend (VISIT) and next weekend) and finals are on monday the 12th and wednesday the 14th (I'M HOME THAT DAY AT 10AM!!!!)

in honor of not doing it in forever - it's time for YOUS!! some may not necessarily have LJ but read this:

you(s) - don't realize i don't like you
you - i miss you - i feel like our friendship is fading away, that scares me because i need you now.
you - you're different. it seems like you don't have time for me anymore.
you - have been amazing this year - and just are amazing. 
you - have hurt me so much this year when you're suppose to be helping me.
you - i am so glad you're out of my life. it's the biggest weight that has been lifted from my shoulders all year and has made me really happy.
you - you're confused about a lot right now - but i'm tired of that being an excuse for everything.
you - where are you?
you - need to leave me alone.
you - suck.


and you (my iPod - yes, i'm doing a YOU about my iPod - shut up) - are the greatest gift i've ever recieved. you have gotten me through this rough semester. our year and a half anniversary just passed and i celebrated by filling you up.
you are my god. i love you more than words can say.





so yeah. me. home. december 14th 10-11am.


call me, bitches.

xoxo ♥

just got back from philosophy. it ended up being a huge debate on what the point of philosophy is. some girl raised her hand and was like "i dont see the point in philosophy" and that just started a riot between the philosophy majors, the teacher and everyone else. it was entertaining. now i'm getting my article for sociology. i'm going to figure out what jobs you can get if you have a sociology degree, and perhaps major in it. i doubt i'll do anything w/that degree except open my own bar (which is my main goal), but whatever. well, not just a bar, an awesome bar with awesome bands every night and just this cool place to come out and hang. kind of like on the OC where alix worked...except it'll be cooler b/c it's mine. and there won't be any VIP rooms, everyone is VIP, fuck celebrities they can come and hang, but they're not getting special treatment...obviously this goal won't be conquered and i'll probably go broke trying to pursue it, but oh well. it's a dream...and what's any life w/o the pursuit of a dream? (that's from vanilla sky). anyways, today. sociology - awesome. acting - bleh. same shit. sleep :-D i'm exhausted. i can't seem to catch up on sleep. OHHHH MAN i am getting a sweet new cell phone tmr. it's a camera phone so i want to take everyone's pictures so when they call it pops up. i have a job for you i'm getting 3 rings. california by phantom planet (The OC theme...obviously), Larger than life by the backstreet boys (b/c i'm awesome), and Last Goodbye by Jeff Buckely. I was going to use last goodbye for just texts, but i think i'll use something else for that. WHICH RING DO YOU WANT, BITCHES? let me know, if you don't then you're getting whatever the hell i feel like. alright, time to read the NY Times new york in 8 DAYS!!

holy shit. 

the series finale of six feet under was by far the most amazing ending to a show ever. it had to be. 

i have never cried harder at a movie or tv show. i'm still going. 


damn, that was fucking awesome.

well....12 days till school i believe? weird. very very weird. this week was good times. monday hung out w/the girls. tuesday hung out w/jake and brendan from his play. we watched that new show "weeds" and it was good, i thought. then we watched "breakfast club" which i'd never seen before -i liked it! wednesday...wow. that was an amazing night (which i'll have pictures of up soon on my yahoo site -- if you dont know it ask for it - they're hilarious ) me, siena and ashley were at the track and we decided to go to woodys w/gildea. so we called him up and were like lets go to woodys! so we went - we had a mini dance party in the car - w/gildeas amazing mixes (if you didn't know he was gay take a look at the songs on those cds - jesus, every other song is like ABBA and he had the RuPaul covergirl song...it was funny). it was so last minute which was why it was so great. so we go there and go in the under 21 room and it's dead. so we go in the boys room - thinking there isn't a girls room - and take pictures at the urinals and stuff - it was funny, like i said - check out the site. then, after meeting some various bisexual and homosexual men and women, it got REALLY packed. so we started dancing w/gildea and his two guy friends Clay and...shit i forget the other guys name - but he was great too. things were getting a little out of hand and sweaty - but it was one of the most fun nights i 've had in a while. the thursday morning i went down the shore to avalon w/my mom sister and marissa - it was nice. we went to my mom's friends house w/her kids. i ended up having to watch the kids for a lot of the time on the beach and that was annoying at times - but i had a good time overall. yesterday afternoon my sister and i went to the wildwood boardwalk and played fasination for 2 hours and spent $40. it was a great time. i won a marilyn purse and we got marissa a bear. we bonded a bit - it was nice. then i came home and went out w/ash, siena, annie, matt, tim, chris, bergels, brennan, and i think that's it - and we went to watch planes take off - granted our seats weren't the best - but playing good music and being w/good people is what it's all about when your days are numbered as mine are. it was a great time. i saw brennan's naked ass....that was....interesting to say the LEAST. we then went to wendys and that was nice, but it really hurt my jaw which i guess isn't completely healed. then i dropped off bergels and had to take klanecks to get his car at matts and we pull up and matt's laying on his lawn so me and klanecki (after a much deserved "Matt this is why you're awesome" comment klanecki made) we layed down w/him and just listened to the summer sounds and the hum of the sexy sati. it was a good time. but damn, am i going to miss these people. today - going to some partays. then hanging out w/my boy b/c i feel i've been neglecting him and i miss his face. hope everyone's summer is ending on a great note. i know mine is.

after last night i can safely say i'm a woman who believes in god again...





and that god's name is CHRIS MARTIN. 





what a fucking amazingly awesome show. 


holy. shit.



yep, it was great.

bleh. work today at 6am. he sent me home early though so only 3.5 hours of agony instead!! yay! last night i ended up going out. i wasn't going to, but i decided that steph and siena are only home for a bit and since the person who ruined last week for me isn't there, i should take full advantage. me, jason gibbs, steph and ashley drove around for like 2 hours last night. we went all up route 1 and ended up in west chester. we were going to feed horses carrots, but all we found were cows....oh, and my dad's house. he has so many cars - bastard. yesterday mom and i went to the mac store in the christiana mall and i got my $30 printer/copier/scanner. -- it's sweet. dude, i leave a month from yesterday i also get my wisdom teeth out friday all 4...bleh ew. it's gonna be ok though. oh my new guilty obsession -- the OC. amazing. sorry it's good. i love adam brody...he reminds me of jake. i hate mischa barton. she sucks. today - steph's pool tonight - dinner w/jake tomorrow - work 7-12 then basically free week till friday! holla!

that is all.

this week has been good. i've been hanging out w/people, ya know. whatev. good times. jake's shows were really good. he was sooooo good. he song was definietly the best. went down the shore friday night w/ash and annie. we hung out and went on the beach till like 3:30am then just hung around until we finally went to bed. stayed on the beach all day and ashley and i were the last ones home having spent almost 7 hours on the beach -- beautiful. it's getting harder and harder to go down there. i mean my money is tight, the rides are just horrible, i'm tired when i get down there, and most of all - i don't get along w/the guys in the house. granted, mark is leaving soon and him and i have never really had "words", but sherman and drew i just don't mix well with. i also hate their parties. i hate the people who graudated like 2 years ago who show up, i hate the smell of the house in the morning, i hate how people are smoking pot in the room i'm trying to sleep in and all the shit that comes with their stupid parties. it may sound like i'm the most straight edge, tight ass person - but i'm really not. i can party and get along with people - but the thing is, i did it all senior week and a few weekend in between, and it's like - i'm tired of seeing those same old faces of people i could care less about - the SHS people who have nothing better to do w/their time than to show up at a senior house. they're assholes. i cant even try and drink and have a good time most of the time because i'm so disgusted by other people's behavior. sorry to bitch, it's just really bothersome that to visit my friends i have to be put through this bullshit that i just can't get the hang of. i don't think it's me being close minded - i can handle people. i can be polite and know i hate them. that's fine. but there's only so much a person can take, that's all i'm saying. now that that's done i found a roommate for west chester. her name is meghan, we met at orientation, she's awesome. simply put. the year is looking good. OH AND ALSO -- I GOT A FACEBOOK -- FRIEND ME!
ah hem.... I GOT A TATTOO. that is all.

wow senior party was so much fun. 


just sad. i was looking at all of the seniors and you look and see all the friends you went through and the phases they were there for, and how that's all over. they're not all going to be there any more. after tomorrow i might never see them ever again. 

it's weird more than anything else. 



oh geez. graduation is going to be harder than expected. 



sheesh.

i forgot to make this annoucement earlier. 



jake got me coldplay tix for graduating. 220 section - that's good enough for me. 



got the album yesterday.....fucking awesome. 




that is all.
I AM DONE HIGH SCHOOL FOREVER!!!!!! ...funny how that hasn't set in just yet.

senior awards. 

good stuff. 

i got the 2 big theater awards including the medallion one. smix, vice, cecil, chris k and dave all got ones too. that was awesome. 

gildea gave great speeches about us all and made me tear up and dr. kelly stopped him from doing the whole speech b/c they were running over. 


some how i managed to get a leadership pin and citizenship pin - that's hot. 


SHS knows i like the accessories for my cap and gown...holla. 


oh and 50$ for the theater award -- fuckin' right. 

we would have more but we literally have like 2$ in the account.


i am glad that i not only had an amazing senior show to make me realize how important theater was, but to have these awards. they really made the little amount of money from not be able to work, stress, fights, drama in the drama and tears pay off into something indescribable. 

i'm a theater geek and always will be at heart. 


thank you to all of you who touched my life by sharing the same hobby as me and being in the same amazing performances with me. you have all impacted me in one way or another and for that i will always love you.

senior solo... not so good. actually quite horrible. but that's ok, it was good to see everyone's creativity shine last night. 


and it was even more amazing to see all the alumni who came back. i loved seeing all the old faces. i miss them. 





heard the band playing the graduation song - whatever that song is - gave me butterflies - i am soooooooo excited!
